title: check empty value to avoid NPE when trying to set the path to null
body: When trying to set the chaincodePath to null, a NPE is fired because of validation. Since the value is not initialized to null, there is no way to bypass the fixed check. Accepting empty string, the check will pass if no chaincodePath has been set at all.

title: fix null rules
body: `chaincodePath` cannot be null in the current implementation (getter will prevent returning null value). Therefore the sanity check for null will always fail, because at best chaincodePath will be empty string. It happens only for Java chaincode that is not officially supported. But this change would help anyone that dares to try.
